-- Almarai, Advanced Petrochemicals, Ash-Sharqiyah: Saudi Preview
-- B y   G l e n   C a r e y
-- 2012-04-28T07:16:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-28/almarai-advanced-petrochemicals-ash-sharqiyah-saudi-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
be active in Saudi Arabia’s market. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are from the last close.  The  Tadawul All Share Index (SASEIDX)  gained 0.4 percent to 7,541.50
on April 25.  Advanced Petrochemicals Co. (APPC)  : The Saudi maker of
polypropylene products is studying opening a joint-venture in
Turkey with an unidentified Turkish partner. The stock advanced
0.8 percent to 26.6 riyals.  Almarai Co. (ALMARAI)  : Saudi Arabia’s largest food
producer said production from an infant formula plant in al-
Kharj, Saudi Arabia, will start during the first week of May.
The shares were unchanged at 64.25 riyals.  Ash-Sharqiyah Development Co. (ASACO)  : The Saudi
developer of agricultural projects in the Eastern Province said
it dismissed General Manager Ahmed al-Sowayegh due to losses and
poor financial results. The shares fell 1.7 percent to 57.25
riyals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Glen Carey in Riyadh at 
 gcarey8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
